{"/service/ndnp/mnhi/batch_mnhi_desdemona_ver01/data/sn82002441/00517012063/1924043001/0217.xml":{"full_text":"L. LOFBERG, LOFBERG CO.\nGENERAL CONTRACTING\nStucco and Concrete Work. House Moving.\nPhones 277 and 112\nEXCELSIOR FURNACES\nPIPE ANU PIPELESN\nIf you are building a new home or remodeling the old one. In\nvestigate. All kinds of builders sheet metal work.\nGRAND RAPIDS\nAUTO SHEET METAL RADIATOR WORKS\nN. P. Kiuca, Prop.\n\nTALK WITH\nWESTON\nABOUT SIGNS\nObserve sign work on trucks of Itasca Co-operative Creamery,\nJohnsen's Sanitary Grocery and the Litchke Feed Store.\nNOW!\nIs the time to have the alterations made in your heating and\nplumbing systems that you have intended doing for so long. We\nhave a choice assortment of strictly modern baths, sinks, toilets,\nlavatories, laundry tubs, etc. Let us help you select the fixtures\nespecially designed for your needs.\nA Water Softener\nYou may also need a water softener to prevent the accumulation\nof scale in the water front and furnace coil. Come in and see us\nabout this problem. Prices are right and all work first class.\nGATES WISE\nPlumbing and Heating\nPhone 90\nA Suggestion\nFor Home Builders\nIf you are planning to build a new home this year,\nor remodel the old one, take our advice and make pro\nvision for all the modern, time and labor saving elec\ntrical appliances.\nYou will alw'ays regret it if you do not make full\nprovision for this work. You need not buy all the ap\npliances now, but be sure and have your wiring done\nin such a way that all future needs will be fully taken\ncare of.\nOur experience enables us to know what you will\nrequire in the next few years. Consult with us before\nbuilding.\nELECTRIC SERVICE COMPANY\nF. H. Johnston Telephone 138\nPainting and Decorating\nThe time is here to clean up and paint up\nCall on us for paper hanging, painting\nand decorating. First class mechanics.\nItasca Auto Paint Shop\nPhone 25\nFinancing Your\nHome\nThe Citizens\u2019 Building Loan Association of Grand\nRapids is ready to give reasonable assistance to pros\npective home builders.\nDo not assume that financial difficulties will make\nit necessary for you to postpone the desired building\nprogram, until you have consulted us on the question.\nThis is a Grand Rapids institution, backed by Grand\nRapids people, and its services are for the benefit of\nGrand Rapids people who know the advantages of\nbuilding homes for themselves.\nAsk for Mr. Spang at the offices of the association, in\nthe First National Bank building.\nCITIZENS\u2019\nBUILDING LOAN ASSOCIATION\nof Grand Rapids, Minnesota\nBuilding Costs\nWill building costs be substantially reduced? Nobody\nknows. To pose as a prophet is running a long chance\nof being proved a fool. Yet certain facts are plain.\nFor a period of years before the great war, building costs\nwere gradually and consistently rising. While the war\nwas on, building was suspended. Followed a sudden\nand unprecedented boom, then a deep and widespread\n\u201c\u201cbusiness depression, and now a healthier and more\nnormal situation.\nThe wages of labor represent, directly or indirectly, 90\nper cent of the cost of building a house. The raw ma\nterials are cut in the woods or dug from the earth by\nlabor. All the way up from the tree, the ore, the clay\npit, the coal mine, labor cuts, and digs and fabricates\nthe lumber, the brick, the hardware. Labor transports\nand assembles the materials. It builds the house. La\nbor costs will always be merely the \u201cwhole thing\u201d in\nbuilding.\nDuring the war and immediately after, wages were large\nly increased. In 1921 came a period of deflation and\nprofound business depression. Building operations\nwere largely suspended. Yet during that period, when\nunemployment was widespread, wages dropped on an\naverage only about 5 per cent.\nNow, business conditions are more nearly normal. There\nis little or no unemployment. There is an increased\ndemand for new building. And it seems to be a fact\nthat in some of the building trades fewer skilled work\nmen are available than ten years ago.\nIt hardly seems possible, therefore, that there can be any\ngreat drop in the wages of the building trades. And\nwithout a considerable decrease in labor costs, no sub\nstantial reduction in building costs is possible.\nThis is not a prediction. It is a conclusion based on cer\ntain facts. It may be wrong. Nobody knows.\nAN \u201cEASY TO UNDERSTAND\u201d EXPLANATION OF\nAVERAGE BUILDING COSTS DISTRIBUTION.\n20-1\nExcavating, Stone, Brick, and Concrete Work.\n17.0%\n15.6%\nMiscellaneous Labor.\n14 9 Heating. Plumbing,\nWiring, and Electrical Fixtures.\n10.1% Screens, Insurance, Permit. Con\ntractor, Miscellaneous.\n8.2% Millwork (including door and window\ncasings, finishing, etc.)\n5.9% Painting, Decorating, and Shades.\n5.5% Plastering.\n\u25a0\u25a0\u25a0\u25a0l 2.7% Sheet Metal and Hardware.\npr\u2014\nNOTE\u2014These figures are average and in different communities va\nriations might be expected.\nNext Week\u2014\u201cA Little Lesson in Thrift.\u2019*\nTo Those Who Plan To\nBuild In 1924:\nThere is no better time to begin your: planning than right NOW \u2014Not\nnext summer or next fall when labor will be scarce and transportation\ncongested.\nExperts agree that 1924 will see a general revival in all lines of busi\nness. This general activity will require vast quantities of labor of\nwhich there is no excess at the present time.\nThe best way to get ahead of this labor condition is to get your plans\nready now and get your new home under way. Those who take ad\nvantage of the early spring months will be mighty glad, later in the\nyear, that they did so.\nMake your wife and family happy plan\ning right now to \u201cOwn Your Own Home.\u201d\nWe invite you to call at BUILDING HEADQUARTERS and let us show\nyou our large and complete stock.\nKING LUMBER CO.\nPhone No. 9\nTips from Taylor\u2014\nWhen we are ill we con- modeled house, get a\nsuit a doctor. If our teeth plumber on the job and he\nache we call on the dentist will plan with you.\nand should our Pierce-Ar- How much space is\nrow refuse to run we call a needed for a bathroom?\nmechanic. We never ask can tell you. What is\nthe butcher to get an esti- t e i oca ti O n for fix\nmate from the garage as to t ures Qur many years of\nwhat it will cost to repair experience in planning\ntne car. plumbing and heating in\nWhen you want an esti- old and new buildings is at\nmate on plumbing and your disposal at no cost to\nheating in your new or re- you.\nMort Taylor\nPlumbing and Heating\nA Store For\nHome Builders\nWe offer to home builders our new and enlarged\nstocks of hardware, stoves, rugs, furniture and com\nplete home furnishings.\nPractically everything you will need in the way of\nequipping and furnishing your new or remodeled home,\nwill be found here.\nAnd you can rely on it that everything you buy here\nis of dependable quality.\nLAWN AND GARDEN TOOLS,\nCLEANERS, PAINT, VARNISH\nKremer Furniture Hardware Co.\nA thing that can\u2019t\nbe slighted\u2014\nThe selection of the most appropriate and the most\neconomical electrical fixtures, and their installation is\none of most important parts of planning your new home\nor remodeling and improving the old one.\nLet us talk with you about your work. We know\nfrom experience where you will want the extra plugs\nand appliances, and we guarantee any electrical work\nwe do as being strictly first class, and dependable.\nNo charge for suggestions or estimates.\nSWANSON ELECTRIC COMPANY\nPhone 169\nGoing to Build\nor Rebuild?\nIt will pay you to select hardware of good quality and\ndesign that you will not tire of. Our long experience\nwill prove of value to the man who is going to build or\nrepair. We have always taken pride in carrying good\nquality merchandise because it gives you better ser\nvice and satisfaction. Come in and talk over your re\nquirements with us. Builders\u2019 Hardware, Roofing,\nShingles, House Paints, Flat Paints, Varnishes, Glass,\nTools, Electrical Supplies, Hot Air Furnaces, etc.\nH. D. POWERS\nThe \u201cWINCHESTER\u201d Store\nHomes or \u201cHomes\u201d?\nHave you ever visited an Old Folks\u2019 Home? What a heart\nbreaking thing it is to see the pitiful attempts of these poor old\npeople to give the few square feet of space they can call their\nown a touch of the real home they once knew.\nAnd they call such places, \u201chomes\u201d! The places where the poor,\nthe sick, the deaf, the blind, the orphans and other public charges\nare housed. Shelters only\u2014compared with real homes such as\nmost of them formerly had.\nMore real homes and fewer \u201chomes\u201d are what this country needs\nright now. The welfare of the individual, the family, the nation,\nthe whole world is based upon homes- Civilization itself is founded\nupon the home. Have you a real home or just a roof and four\nwalls\nLook at your home. Think about it. What can you do to make\nit better? Home surroundings exert such a tremendous influence\nover family life.\nBetter homes mean better children. Better children mean better\nmen and women. Better men and women mean better citizens.\nAnd better citizens mean better America.\nCity Lumber Company\nA. W. Sitz, Manager","height":"28077","width":"20991"}}
